-- SITC International Said to Raise $400 Million in Hong Kong Initial Offer
-- B y   F o x   H u
-- 2010-09-28T10:41:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/sitc-international-said-to-raise-400-million-in-initial-public-offering.html
SITC International Holdings Co. ,
which offers shipping and logistics services, raised HK$3.1
billion ($400 million) selling shares in an initial public
offering in Hong Kong, according to two people with knowledge of
the transaction.  The Shanghai-based company sold 650 million shares at
HK$4.78 each, the low end of its offer range, said the people,
who declined to be identified because the information was
private. SITC initially offered its shares at HK$4.78 to HK$6.28
each, according to the company’s IPO prospectus.  Citigroup Inc.  and  China International Capital Corp. 
managed the transaction. SITC is the biggest privately owned
container-line operator in China, with a total capacity last
year of 1.18 million standard cargo boxes, according to the
company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fox Hu in Hong Kong at 
 fhu7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
